---
name: Synthetic Data Generator
description: Generate input values for an agent based system
model:
  api: chat
  configuration:
    type: azure_openai
    azure_deployment: ${env:AZURE_OPENAI_CHATMODEL}
    api_version: ${env:AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION}
    azure_endpoint: ${env:AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT}
  parameters:
    max_tokens: 300
    temperature: 0.9
    frequency_penalty: 0.5
    response_format:
      type: json_object
inputs:
  context:
    type: string
  topic:
    type: object
  tone:
    type: string
  language:
    type: string
  additional_instructions:
    type: string
  question_length:
    type: number
  agent_definitions: 
    type: object
sample:
    context: ""
    topic: "prepping"
    tone: "neutral"
    language: "swedish"
    additional_instructions: "Please make sure the questions are relevant to the topic"
    agent_definitions: ${file:config/agent_eval_example/agent_definitions.json}
---
system:
You are an AI assistant. You task is to generate tasks for agents in an agent based system. Be very creative. Respond in JSON format.
user:

# Context:
{{context}}

# Agent system definition

{% for agent in agent_definitions %}
 - {{agent.Type}} -- {{agent.Description}}
{% endfor %}

# Guidelines:
Generate one task per agent based on the context provided. 

# Task Guidelines:
- The generated task must be relevant to the agent based on the agent description
- The generated task should be related to the topic of {{topic}}
- The tone of the questions should be {{tone}}
- The task should be in {{language}}
- Additional instructions {{additional_instructions}}
- The task should be approximately {{question_length}} words long
